The paper deals with privacy and security of face images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The proposed architecture involves training a neural network, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a pseudo gender classifier and a pseudo face matcher, which are common tools in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
